  "prompt": "Which problems should I attempt first on TopCoder?",
  "response": "When starting on TopCoder, it's recommended to follow this progression:\n\n1. Beginner Level\n- Start with DIV 2 250-point problems\n- Focus on problems involving:\n  - Basic string manipulation\n  - Simple arithmetic\n  - Easy array processing\n  - Basic logic and conditionals\n\n2. Initial Learning Path\n- Practice problems in these categories:\n  - Simple math\n  - String parsing\n  - Basic data structures\n  - Simple simulation problems\n  - Easy greedy algorithms\n\n3. Recommended First Problem Types\n- Classic beginner problems like:\n  - FizzBuzz variants\n  - String reversals\n  - Digit sum calculations\n  - Basic array transformations\n  - Simple counting problems\n\n4. Early Skill Development\n- Learn to read problem statements carefully\n- Practice translating problem descriptions into code\n- Focus on clean, readable solutions\n- Start with languages like C++, Java, or Python\n\n5. Resources to Use\n- TopCoder's Practice Rooms\n- SRM (Single Round Match) archives\n- Problem archives sorted by difficulty\n- Online tutorials and solution explanations\n\nGradually increase difficulty as you gain confidence and problem-solving skills.",
